  "texts": [
    "In this study we introduced DART-FISH, a high throughput RNA in situ mapping technique, and demonstrated its application to human tissues, even with high native autofluorescence background.",
    "In the human brain, we recovered the spatial distribution of 20 cell types from the 3 main cell classes.",
    "This included the laminar organization of the excitatory neurons in the cortex and the broader layer-specificity of inhibitory neurons, and the ubiquity of the nonneuronal cells across the brain cortex.",
    "We also profiled a sample from a histopathologically abnormal human kidney and demonstrated identification of rare cells such as REN-producing cells, the intricate functional niches, and quantified the interactions between pathological cell states.",
    "DART-FISH is a cost-effective technology capable of fast decoding on relatively large tissue sections."
  ],
